19 Careful Calculus Guides Obama Administration in Health Insurance Projections 
The New York Times: WASHINGTON — In April 2014, President Obama declared victory in the government’s aggressive push to enroll people in private health insurance plans under the Affordable Care Act, announcing that eight million people had signed up for coverage.
